headline.print_headline: Key Commander of ISIS Is Killed by U.S. Forces
headline.main: A Top ISIS Leader Is Killed in an Airstrike, the Pentagon Says

snippet: The killing of Abd al-Rahman Mustafa al-Qaduli comes as the U.S. appears to be having increased success targeting the Islamic State’s leadership.
abstract: Top Islamic State commander Abd al-Rahman Mustafa al-Qaduli is killed by American forces in eastern Syria; military officials say group is losing ground, despite recent violent attacks in Western Europe, as it loses leaders, infantry and funding.
